Class SWLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.monash.fit2099.simulator.space.Location
      • starwars.SWLocation

  • public class SWLocation
extends Location
    Class that models locations in Star Wars.

    SWLocations are not restricted to 8-way movements.

    Author:
    ram

        public char getSymbol()
        Returns a character that represents this SWLocation.

        Returns:

      • setSymbol

        public void setSymbol(char c)
        Sets the character symbol of this SWLocation to a new character c.

        The Views use this symbols to query for resources(images of texture) and for display, hence although not a must symbols of different types of SWLocations are preferably unique.
